# MVC: Entity Management

MVC: Entity Management - this is a common functionality for ORM (Models) and ODM (Mongo Collections).
Using this feature you can implement your own ODM/ORM (eg. ODM for CouchDB).

!!! IMPORTANT !!! This feature has full backward compatibility!

This is very handy if you want to write a module that can work with different databases.
Eg.

``` php
interface UserInterface extends \Phalcon\Mvc\EntityInterface
{
    // some additional code here
}
```

Implements as collection:

``` php
class UserCollection extends \Phalcon\Mvc\Collection implements UserInterface
{
    // some additional code here
}
```

Implements as model:

``` php
class UserModel extends \Phalcon\Mvc\Model implements UserInterface
{
    // some additional code here
}
```

Using #1:

``` php

$user = DI::getDefault()->get('newuserinstance');
// i don't know the $user is model or collection or something else.
if ($user instanceof \Phalcon\Mvc\EntityInterface) {
  // i can do it :)
  $user->writeAttribute('name', 10);
  $name = $user->readAttribute('name');
  $user->create();
  $user->update();
  $user->save();
  $user->delete();  
}

if ($user instanceof \Phalcon\Mvc\StaticFinderInterface) {
  $users = $user::find(['limit' => 10]);
}

```

Using #2:

``` php
class Example
{
    public function deleteUser(UserInterface $user)
    {
        // I do not care, it is a model or a collection, or something else. I need to remove! :)
        $status = $user->delete(); 

        echo $status? 'ok' : 'not deleted';
    }
}

$example = new Example();
$dbUser = UserModel::findFirst();
$mongoUser = UserCollection::findFirst();

$example->deleteUser($dbUser); // ok
$example->deleteUser($mongoUser); // ok
```

